  "vulnerability_information": "## Summary:\nThe application claims to disallow hyperlinks in the Biography field with the notice:\n`Links are forbidden.`\nHowever, it is possible to bypass this restriction using a protocol-relative URL (//evil.com) in an <a> tag. This allows an attacker to embed external links despite the stated limitation, violating trust and posing security risks.\n\n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\n1. Log in to the website `https://addons.allizom.org`\n2. Click on `edit profile`\n\n{F4409242}\n\n3. In the `Biography` field, there will be a warning that\n`Some HTML supported: <abbr title> <acronym title> <b> <blockquote> <code> <em> <i> <li> <ol> <strong> <ul>. Links are forbidden.`\n\n{F4409247}\n\n4. Now, we add the <a> tag\n\n##payload: `<a href=\"//evil.com\">click</a>`\n\n{F4409262}\n\n5. Check that this <a> tag is executed. and when clicking on `click` will redirect to the page `http://evil.com/`\n{F4409264}\n\n{F4409267}\n\n## Impact\n\n- Violates declared application policy: users trust that links are not allowed.\n- Enables attackers to embed links to:\n- Phishing sites.\n- Malware downloads.\n- Social engineering payloads.",
  "weakness": {
    "id": 107,
    "name": "Improper Input Validation"
  },
